post_text: The Meadow Heights Booster Club will be hosting a golf tournament at Bent Creek Golf Course on June 28th. You can sponsor a hole for $100, donate door prizes or come out and join us for a day of golf. It will be a four-person scramble, $320 per team. They will offer skins and Mulligans for purchase at registration as well as a poker run, 50/50 drawing and move up option on hole 12. It will be a shotgun start at 8:30 a.m. and we will serve lunch afterwards where we will draw for door prizes and announce winners. Please contact me at 573-208-9344 for more information.

post_text:
Tonight‚Äôs Game Vs Leopold
A benefit for the Deck‚Äôs- Tonight
Meadow Heights will play Leopold in a high school basketball game, but this night will be about much more than a game, as we will be hosting a benefit for the family of a former player of mine Mason Deck, whose families house was lost to a fire at Christmas this year. We will have a 50/50 raffle, a silent auction for baked goods, and asking that you bring a household item that the family could use, or clothing for entry to the game. Sizes on clothes are listed below. This will be a great night of both family and basketball. If you would like to donate a baked good or have any questions contact myself or Candy Wilfong 573 275-7888.
